The Veterans Benefits Administration is responsible for the administration of the following programs of the Department:(1) Compensation and pension programs.

(2) Vocational rehabilitation and educational assistance programs.

(3) Veterans’ housing loan programs.

(4) Veterans’ and servicemembers’ life insurance programs.

(5) Outreach programs and other veterans’ services programs.

(Added Pub. L. 102–83, § 2(b), Aug. 6, 1991, 105 Stat. 399.)</akn:p></akn:content><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7703_1"><akn:num>(1)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(1) Compensation and pension programs.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7703_2"><akn:num>(2)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(2) Vocational rehabilitation and educational assistance programs.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7703_3"><akn:num>(3)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(3) Veterans’ housing loan programs.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7703_4"><akn:num>(4)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(4) Veterans’ and servicemembers’ life insurance programs.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7703_5"><akn:num>(5)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(5) Outreach programs and other veterans’ services programs.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>